-- Vodacom Chief Operating Officer Maseko Quits for Other Interests
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2012-06-14T15:21:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/vodacom-chief-operating-officer-maseko-quits-for-other-interests.html
Vodacom Group Ltd. (VOD) , the largest
provider of wireless services to South Africans, said Chief
Operating Officer Sipho Maseko resigned to pursue other
interests.  Maseko, who joined the company in September, was also
managing director of Vodacom South Africa, the Johannesburg-
based company said in an e-mailed statement today. A further
announcement will be made “in due course,” it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vernon Wessels in Johannesburg at 
